thread.title: Rupee gains in early trade as exporters sell dollars
thread.title_full: Rupee gains in early trade as exporters sell dollars | Business Standard News

author: Press Trust of India
title: Rupee gains in early trade as exporters sell dollars
text:
The rupee rose by 14 paise at 66.02 against the US dollar in early trade today on fresh selling of the American currency by exporters.

A higher opening in the domestic equity market supported the rupee, but the US dollar's rise against other currencies capped the gains.

The rupee had dropped 18 paise against the US dollar to close at 66.16 against the greenback on Thursday.

Forex market were closed on Friday on account of "Bakr Id".

Meanwhile, the benchmark BSE Sensex was trading higher by 73.39 points, or 0.28%, at 25,936.89 in early trade.
